  "prompt": "Which is the best college in India for doing mech engineering except for the IITs?",
  "response": "While the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) are highly regarded, there are several other prestigious institutions in India for mechanical engineering. Some of the best colleges include:\n\n1. **Birla Institute of Technology and Science (BITS), Pilani**: Renowned for its academic rigor and excellent campus facilities.\n  \n2. **National Institute of Technology (NIT), Tiruchirappalli**: Often ranked as one of the top NITs in India, known for strong faculty and research opportunities.\n  \n3. **Delhi Technological University (DTU), Delhi**: Offers a strong engineering program with good industry connections and placement opportunities.\n  \n4. **Vellore Institute of Technology (VIT), Vellore**: Known for its competitive entrance exam, modern campus, and high placement rate.\n  \n5. **Indian Institute of Engineering Science and Technology (IIEST), Shibpur**: One of the oldest engineering colleges in India with a rich heritage in engineering education.\n\nEach of these institutions has its unique strengths, so the best choice may depend on your specific criteria such as location, campus facilities, faculty expertise, research opportunities, and placement records.",
